comments.text:
NEVER buy the expensive max plans, this is useless. Claude Code DOES NOT work on big projects, let alone small projects. It works only on ultra-small things, and is certainly not ready for real production projects. Don't let yourself be fooled by the misleading marketing.
Giving 100$ or 200$ for that is a total non-sense. Claude Code is still unable to keep track correctly of long conversations, which renders it useless for large projects, even small ones.
The only way of making it work correctly is by using extreme babysitting, and even that way, you will have to constantly repeat the sames things, despite the existing mechanisms for including instructions automatically.
It's a gfreat tech, but absolutely not usable in real producitons. It works on a subset of mainstream programming languages, and is not aware of recent versions of libraries. It has web search capabilities, but far insuficient to close the gap to newer versions of libs.
Gemini is far from perfect, but with its 1 millions tokens context length, it solves 50% of Claude Code problems. It actually read files entirely and keep them in contexte, whereas Claude Code use 65 tool calls to read small bits of files here and there. Gemini cli is free. Never put 100 or 200$ for a cli, lol
